Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} onto a
#baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and sprinkle on the
@Thai style spice mix{1%packet}. Use your hands to rub the seasoning all over.
Arrange in one even layer and roast until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the @water{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp}.
Bring to the boil and once boiling, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}. Lower the
heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes},
then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for
another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in
its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Chop into 2cm sized chunks, trim the @pak choi{1}. Separate the leaves
and quarter widthways into roughly 2cm chunks. Trim the @green beans{80%g} and
chop into thirds. Zest then cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Roughly chop the
@coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir-fry the
pepper and green beans until beginning to soften and colour, ~{4-5%minutes}.
Stir in the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} to coat and cook for ~{1%minute}.
Add the pak choi along with the @coconut milk{200%ml} and the
@water{75%ml}. Bring to the boil then turn the heat to medium-low.

Let the curry simmer until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. When the
cauliflower is ready, add it to the curry along with the @king prawns{150%g}
and stir to coat in the sauce. Simmer until the prawns are cooked through,
~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and
opaque in the middle. Remove from the heat and stir in the @soy sauce{12.5%ml}.
Squeeze in some lime juice. Taste and add more, salt, pepper and lime juice if
you feel it needs it. Fluff up the rice and stir in the lime zest and half the
coriander.

Share the rice between your #bowls{} and top with the fragrant curry. Finish
with a sprinkle of the remaining coriander. Serve the remaining lime wedges
alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!

> If you've added prawns to your recipe, in the step above, when you add the
> cauliflower to the recipe, add the prawns too and stir to coat in the sauce.
> Simmer until the prawns are cooked through, 3-4 mins. IMPORTANT: The prawns are
> cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Continue with the
> recipe as instructed.